[2026-03-08T04:07:09Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016yKpxhVHv4TtqCEH8LUPHp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully found the code related to the **\"Project Info Page\"** with its **\"Prompts section\"** that features expansion/collapse arrows. Here are the key files and code sections:\n\n### Main Files:\n\n1. **HTML Template** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n2. **Go Handler** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n3. **CSS Styles** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n---\n\n### Project Info Page Architecture:\n\n#### Template Structure (project_detail.html, lines 25-29):\nThe page contains a **\"Project Info\" panel** that loads dynamically via JavaScript:\n```html\n<!-- Panel 2: Project Info -->\n<div class=\"panel\" id=\"info-panel\">\n    <div class=\"panel-header\">Project Info</div>\n    <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"project-info\">Loading...</div>\n</div>\n```\n\n#### Prompts Section with Expansion (project_detail.html, lines 89-121):\nThe `loadProjectInfo()` function builds HTML containing a **Prompt Files section** with expandable details:\n```javascript\nif (data.prompt_files && data.prompt_files.length > 0) {\n    html += '<h2 style=\"margin-top:1rem\">Prompt Files</h2>';\n    data.prompt_files.forEach(function(pf) {\n        html += '<details><summary class=\"mono\">' + pf.path + '</summary>';\n        if (pf.history && pf.history.length > 0) {\n            html += '<div style=\"margin:0.5rem 0\">';\n            pf.history.forEach(function(h) {\n                html += '<div class=\"prompt-commit\" data-file=\"' + pf.path + '\" data-sha=\"' + h.sha + '\" onclick=\"toggleDiff(this)\" style=\"cursor:pointer;padding:0.25rem 0;font-size:0.85rem\">';\n                html += '<span class=\"mono\" style=\"color:var(--link)\">' + h.sha + '</span> ';\n                html += '<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">' + h.date + '</span> ';\n                html += h.message;\n                html += '</div>';\n            });\n            html += '</div>';\n        } else {\n            html += '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.85rem\">No history</p>';\n        }\n        html += '</details>';\n    });\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Uses native HTML `<details>` and `<summary>` elements (provides built-in expand/collapse with arrow)\n- Shows monospaced file path as the expandable header\n- Each prompt file displays its git commit history inside the expanded section\n- Each commit shows: short SHA (7 chars), date, and commit message\n- Commits are clickable to toggle a diff view\n\n#### Git Commit History & Diff (project_detail.html, lines 123-139):\nThe `toggleDiff()` function fetches and displays diffs for specific commits:\n```javascript\nfunction toggleDiff(el) {\n    var existing = el.nextElementSibling;\n    if (existing && existing.classList.contains('diff-block')) {\n        existing.remove();\n        return;\n    }\n    var file = el.getAttribute('data-file');\n    var sha = el.getAttribute('data-sha');\n    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/info/prompt-diff?file=' + encodeURIComponent(file) + '&sha=' + encodeURIComponent(sha))\n        .then(function(r) { return r.text(); })\n        .then(function(text) {\n            var pre = document.createElement('pre');\n            pre.className = 'diff-block';\n            pre.textContent = text || '(no diff available)';\n            el.parentNode.insertBefore(pre, el.nextSibling);\n        });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Backend API Handlers:\n\n#### 1. **handleAPIProjectInfo** (handler.go, lines 939-1025):\nFetches project information including prompt files and their git history:\n- Reads Docker image from `Dockerfile`\n- Reads version number\n- **Scans `.cloche/prompts/` directory** for all prompt files\n- **Executes git log** for each file to retrieve commit history:\n  ```go\n  cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n  ```\n- Returns JSON with: docker_image, version, and prompt_files array containing path + commit history\n\n#### 2. **handleAPIPromptDiff** (handler.go, lines 1027-1056):\nRetrieves the actual git diff for a specific commit:\n- Takes `file` and `sha` query parameters\n- Executes: `git diff <sha>^..<sha> -- <file>`\n- Returns plain text diff output\n- Includes SHA validation to prevent injection\n\n---\n\n### CSS Styling for Expandable Sections (style.css):\n\n#### Details Element Styling (lines 197-221):\n```css\ndetails {\n    margin: 0.5rem 0;\n}\n\ndetails summary {\n    cursor: pointer;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    color: var(--text-muted);\n}\n\ndetails pre {\n    background: var(--bg-surface);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: var(--radius);\n    padding: 0.75rem;\n    font-family: var(--mono);\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    max-height: 400px;\n    overflow: auto;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    word-break: break-word;\n    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;\n}\n```\n\n#### Diff Block Styling (lines 550-563):\n```css\n.diff-block {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: var(--radius);\n    padding: 0.5rem;\n    font-family: var(--mono);\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    max-height: 300px;\n    overflow: auto;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    word-break: break-word;\n    margin: 0.25rem 0 0.5rem;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Data Flow Summary:\n\n1. User navigates to `/projects/{name}` → renders `project_detail.html`\n2. Page loads, calls `loadProjectInfo()` which fetches `/api/projects/{label}/info`\n3. Backend scans `.cloche/prompts/` directory and runs `git log` for each file\n4. Frontend renders prompt files with native `<details>` elements (built-in arrow expand/collapse)\n5. User clicks a commit line → `toggleDiff()` calls `/api/projects/{label}/info/prompt-diff`\n6. Diff is fetched and inserted into DOM as `.diff-block` element"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a31aa6defd118d061 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46371\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 21689</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66cf5312-1385-4257-ad68-f8904e01f368","uuid":"9d30cc6e-1bf5-4863-8cc4-d01f486abde5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code related to the \"project info page\" and its \"Prompts section\" with expansion arrows. This is likely a TUI/UI component that displays project information including prompts. Look for:\n1. Any files related to \"project info\", \"project detail\", or \"project view\"\n2. Code that handles expansion/collapse of prompt sections\n3. Code that reads or displays prompt file contents\n4. Any reference to git commits being shown in a prompts context\n\nSearch broadly - check internal/, cmd/, and any UI-related directories. Report the full file paths and relevant code sections.","agentId":"a31aa6defd118d061","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully found the code related to the **\"Project Info Page\"** with its **\"Prompts section\"** that features expansion/collapse arrows. Here are the key files and code sections:\n\n### Main Files:\n\n1. **HTML Template** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n2. **Go Handler** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n3. **CSS Styles** — `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n---\n\n### Project Info Page Architecture:\n\n#### Template Structure (project_detail.html, lines 25-29):\nThe page contains a **\"Project Info\" panel** that loads dynamically via JavaScript:\n```html\n<!-- Panel 2: Project Info -->\n<div class=\"panel\" id=\"info-panel\">\n    <div clas